pr.body:
Six CI scenarios failed across two sites: all SauceDemo checkout tests threw `ElementShouldBeEnabledException`, and all Magento search/product-detail tests threw `TimeoutException: Cloudflare SSL error page detected` after exhausting retries.

## SauceDemo — double-dash slug bug

`addProductToCart` was generating malformed button IDs due to a chained replace that inserted double dashes:

```java
// Before: "Sauce Labs Backpack" → "add-to-cart-sauce--labs--backpack" (doesn't exist)
productName.toLowerCase().replace(" ", "--").replace("-", "-")

// After: "Sauce Labs Backpack" → "add-to-cart-sauce-labs-backpack"
productName.toLowerCase().replace(" ", "-")
```

## Magento — Cloudflare retry not triggered for non-526 errors

`isCloudflareSslErrorPage()` required both `cf-error-details` **and** the literal text `"Error code 526"` / `"Invalid SSL certificate"`. Any other Cloudflare 5xx (521 web server down, 522 timeout, 523 unreachable, etc.) returned `false`, so `withCloudflareRetry`'s catch block saw `!isCloudflareSslErrorPage()` and re-threw immediately instead of retrying.

Fix: check only for `cf-error-details`, which is present on every Cloudflare error page:

```java
// Before
return pageSource.contains("cf-error-details")
    && (pageSource.contains("Error code 526") || pageSource.contains("Invalid SSL certificate"));

// After
return pageSource.contains("cf-error-details");
```

A unit test for non-526 Cloudflare error detection (`shouldDetectNonSslCloudflareErrors`) is added to `MagentoHomePageTest`.
